section: Exhibit 10.1 JOINT VENTURE AGREEMENT THIS JOINT VENTURE AGREEMENT (the "Agreement") made and entered into this 20th day of Friday, March 2020 (the "Execution Date"), BETWEEN: BorrowMoney.com, inc of 512 Bayshore DR, suite 201 Fort Lauderdale FL 33304, and JVLS, LLC dba Vaccines 2Go of 4060 Johns Creek Parkway Suite H Suwanee, GA 30024 (individually the "Member" and collectively the "Members").
explanation: The phrase '20th day of Friday, March 2020' is structurally flawed. March 20, 2020, was a Friday, but the inclusion of both the ordinal '20th' and the day of the week 'Friday' is redundant and poor formatting, making the date declaration unconventional and slightly nonsensical. While it doesn't invalidate the agreement, it demonstrates a lack of attention to detail and could potentially be questioned in a dispute, as the structure is not proper and does not make sense in the context of legal documents.

section: Purpose 3. The exclusive purpose of the Venture (the "Purpose") will be IT Development. internet Back office Maintenance And Deployment of medical Service.
explanation: The section describing the 'Purpose' of the venture, which outlines the business's objectives, contains structural flaws. 'IT Development. internet Back office Maintenance And Deployment of medical Service.' lacks proper sentence structure and grammar. The inconsistent capitalization (IT vs. internet), the missing articles (e.g., 'the internet'), and the overall lack of clear phrasing makes it difficult to understand the precise scope of the venture's activities. The lack of proper structuring of the purpose does not make sense and could lead to confusion over the obligations.

explanation: This section showcases misaligned terminology, leading to an in-text contradiction.  BorrowMoney.com, inc contributing '1,500 square feet of Leased/rent office Space Includingspecified Description of duty*' is assigned a value of $3,500,000.00 USD. JVLS, LLC dba Vaccines 2Go contributing '$60,000.00 USD in cash. Plus (10%) Of Any Generated Gross Revenue, In Add i t i on to The To ta l Contributions.' is also assigned a value of $3,500,000.00 USD. It is unclear why the 10% is factored in. Moreover, the different forms of contributions, office space versus cash and revenue sharing, are difficult to compare directly. This discrepancy in valuation and the ambiguity surrounding the revenue share create a contradiction as to the true capital contributions and their respective values.
